Diabetes Treatment Guidelines.
Type 1 diabetes is a chronic condition where the pancreas produces little or no insulin. Therefore, Type 1 diabetes is managed primarily with daily insulin therapy, which can be delivered via multiple daily injections or a continuous insulin pump. Monitoring blood sugar levels is critical.
Type 2 diabetes affects the way the body processes blood sugar. It can often be managed with lifestyle changes such as healthy diet, regular exercise, weight loss, and oral medications like metformin. In some cases, insulin injections may also be required.
endstream
